					<P1 TITLE="Welcome" TYPE="CONTENT">
						<CONTENT>
							<![CDATA[<b>Business Management 2</b><br /><br />Boston City Campus and Business College believes in education for life. Its award-winning institutions have a proven track record of excellence in tertiary training, offering a variety of degrees, diplomas and short courses. With over 40 campuses in South Africa and neighbouring countries, Boston has you covered, and its emphasis on ‘real world experience’ means you can enter the job market with confidence. Moreover, its institutions and campuses understand that education is about developing the individual and nurturing their potential. Each Boston graduate is provided with the knowledge and understanding to fulfil this potential and succeed in their chosen career.<br /><br />Boston City Campus and Business College has the content, facilities and technologies to ensure you receive a world-class education; and its focus on practical experience means that you will be ready to make your mark in the real economy – starting now.<br /><br />Business Management 2 is a practical and comprehensive guide to the basic concepts and principles of strategic management. The purpose of this textbook is to introduce students studying towards a qualification in commerce to the current terminology and concepts which this subject field has to offer.<br /><br />On completion of this course students should be able to:<br /><br />
•	Illustrate a basic understanding of strategic management<br /><br />
•	Formulate a strategic direction for an organisation<br /><br />
•	Understand the context of strategic selection<br /><br />
•	Formulate ‘SMART’ goals and objectives for an organisation<br /><br />
•	Identify and formulate different strategies for an organisation<br /><br />
•	Evaluate and select the most appropriate strategy for an organisation<br /><br />
•	Implement a chosen strategy correctly<br /><br />
•	Continually improve an organisation through strategic control and evaluation<br /><br />
•	Manage strategic changes in an organisation sensitively and with a greater goal in mind<br />]]>
						</CONTENT>
					</P1>
					<P2 TITLE="About EDGE" TYPE="CONTENT" LOCK="true">
							<CONTENT>
							<![CDATA[<b>Welcome to Edge Learning Media – specialists in business school learning media!</b><br /><br />EDGE Learning Media is a dynamic South African business with a visionary and innovative approach to education. Using a full-service publishing model, we are able to design and build bespoke learning content for institutions, training providers and anyone else. This means that our clients come to us with their specific learning material needs, and we endeavour to meet them.<br /><br />We specialise in an extensive range of business school subjects, including (among many others) bookkeeping and accounting, tax, office administration, financial management, human resource management, computyping, end-user computing, business English and business mathematics, business law and accounting control, governance, banking and personal finance.<br /><br />Our learning media includes textbooks, study and solutions guides, workbooks, lecturer guides, CDs, sample assessment question and memorandum preparation and online facilitator and lecturer support.<br /><br />Please do not hesitate to contact us if you have any queries.<br /><br />Edge Learning Media Support Team<br /><br />T: +27 21 702 0686<br />F: +27 86 510 2259<br />E-mail: info@edgelearningmedia.com<br />www.edgelearningmedia.com<br>]]>
